For example, a 2015 <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.karger.com/Article/abstract/362168\\">study</a> revealed that participants who savored a high-protein egg breakfast dropped more weight and were more satiated than participants who had steamed bread.</p><p>\\"Eggs are an excellent breakfast food to incorporate into your diet,\\" Young explains. \\"They are rich in protein (and contain all essential amino acids) and are nutrient-dense, providing a variety of nutrients. They are the foods that make you feel warm, full, nostalgic, and happy. But sometimes those often carb-laden comfort dishes don't always align with certain diets. Additionally, finding <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/foods-to-avoid-keto-diet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">keto-friendly</a> comfort food recipes, in particular, can sometimes prove to be especially difficult.</p><p>The keto diet is a very specific diet plan that involves eating foods that have either no or very few carbohydrates, as well as foods that are high in fat. This helps the body to stay in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ketosis-tips-keto-diet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">ketosis</a>, in which your body doesn't consume enough carbohydrates during the day to burn for energy, so it burns fat instead.</p><p>Followers of the keto diet tend to avoid foods with a lot of sugar in them or those made from grains. However, this can limit your ability to enjoy a lot of classic comfort food dishes.</p><p>Thankfully, there are always workarounds to help make a meal keto-friendly. According to the United Nations, an event constitutes genocide when the aggressors are proven to act toward the total or partial elimination of a specific group or groups of people based on racial, ethnic, religious, or national grounds. Importantly, these programs of elimination don't necessarily have to be carried out through mass murder; the UN provides five methods of elimination that can be called genocide. Killing is the most obvious method, followed by causing serious bodily or mental harm, mandating living conditions with the intent of destroying a group, halting new births in a certain group, and, finally, separating the children of a group from the adults.</p><p><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/community/channel/vid-7xx8mnucu55yw63we9va2gwr7uihbxwc68fxqp25x6tg4ftibpra?cvid=94631541bc0f4f89bfd59158d696ad7e\\">Follow us and access great exclusive content every day</a></p>","image":{"width":1920,"height":1280,"quality":89,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA19OEfI.img","attribution":"Getty Images","title":"How to define a genocide","caption":"<p>The word \\"genocide\\" is thrown around quite often, but it does, in fact, have an exact and explicit definition. Importantly, these programs of elimination don't necessarily have to be carried out through mass murder; the UN provides five methods of elimination that can be called genocide. it\xE2\x80\x99s midday and you realize your stomach is already growling, the last thing you want to do is find a place to get a healthful meal. You\xE2\x80\x99re hungry, and it\xE2\x80\x99s just so convenient to head to the office cafeteria for whatever they have to offer. But if your goal is losing weight, planning healthy lunch ideas for <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/weight-loss/diets/g20440614/25-best-weight-loss-tips-ever/\\">weight loss</a> to have at the ready makes the biggest difference in supporting your goals.</p><p>And skipping out on lunch is never an option. \xE2\x80\x9CIt\xE2\x80\x99s unfair to expect our body or brain to perform at their best if we aren\xE2\x80\x99t providing the fuel they need through food,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://streetsmartnutrition.com/about/\\">Cara Harbstreet, M.S., R.D., L.D.</a>, owner of <a href=\\"http://www.streetsmartnutrition.com\\">Street Smart Nutrition</a>. \xE2\x80\x9CSkipping a mid-day meal eliminates a key opportunity to get essential nutrition or food groups that may not show up in other meals or snacks.\xE2\x80\x9D </p><h2>How to build a healthy lunch for weight loss</h2><p>The most important thing to keep in mind when planning your lunches for the week is choosing foods that taste good to you, make you feel good, and keep you satisfied, says <a href=\\"https://beautifuleatsandthings.com/about/\\">Andrea Mathis, M.A., R.D.N., L.D.N.</a>, author of <a href=\\"https://www.amazon.com/Complete-Book-Smoothies-Healthy-Energize-ebook/dp/B091MDL2J5?tag=syndication-20&ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2141.g.42100898%5Bsrc%7Cmsn-us\\"><em>The Complete Book of Smoothies</em></a>. Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. Your plate should include fiber, fat, and protein to promote the feeling of fullness and manage appetite. One of her favorite ingredients to incorporate into meals is avocados, which have heart-healthy fats and fiber to keep you satisfied. <br>And if you\xE2\x80\x99re struggling with planning lunches that help you reach your goals, Mathis encourages setting realistic and sustainable goals for yourself. \xE2\x80\x9CTo help you stay on track, choose meals that are easy to prepare and set aside a time or day to prep your meals,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Harbstreet adds that you can try \xE2\x80\x9Chabit stacking\xE2\x80\x9D which includes attaching <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/food-nutrition/a20472042/6-protein-packed-meal-prep-recipes/\\">meal prep</a> to a habit you already have. For example, you could prep your lunch as soon as you get home instead of waiting for later when you\xE2\x80\x99d rather be relaxing, she suggests.<br>Ready to get cooking? Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. Your plate should include fiber, fat, and protein to promote the feeling of fullness and manage appetite. One of her favorite ingredients to incorporate into meals is avocados, which have heart-healthy fats and fiber to keep you satisfied. <br>And if you\xE2\x80\x99re struggling with planning lunches that help you reach your goals, Mathis encourages setting realistic and sustainable goals for yourself. \xE2\x80\x9CTo help you stay on track, choose meals that are easy to prepare and set aside a time or day to prep your meals,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. a hectic weeknight, it can be easy for even the most experienced home cook to think of vegetables last \xE2\x80\x94 an afterthought to a roasted chicken or pan-fried salmon. But whether you're spending extra time mastering an entr\xC3\xA9e or simply zapping leftovers in the microwave (pizza included!), a fresh side dish can transform a quick dinner into something seriously memorable. And not all healthy sides need to stop at roasted vegetables. There are plenty of grains that can make a better-for-you bowl feel so much more special, legumes and beans that can make dinner taste quite hearty, and elevated salad ideas that make greens seem like a revelation. </p><p>The best side dishes that are satisfying <em>and</em> healthy lean heavily on nutritional powerhouses that are full of fiber, helping you to feel even more satisfied, all while keeping you running until your next meal (or away from a dreaded midnight snack urge). Versatile staples like broccoli and zucchini are perfect options to soak in plenty of pan drippings and sauces, marrying the flavors of your plate du jour while packing in a punch of fiber. And delicate staples, including tomatoes, cucumbers, and onions, transform a bowl of greens into a culinary work of art that comes together in just a few minutes (perfectly dressed, of course). </p><p>If you're looking to make a bowl of rice or pasta that you can feel good about, try focusing in on some of the grains featured in these recipes. You'll want to double down on quinoa, bulgur, or farro; even whole wheat pasta and gluten-free noodles can be smart options. These hearty bases can also play host to a myriad of vegetables that we simply can't get enough of. Though generally considered a less-than-nutritious treat, <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/healthy-chips/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">some chips are healthier</a> than others, and the unhealthiest chips of all can be especially difficult to resist. If you grab too many bags and nibble on these treats a little too often, you might end up dealing with the <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ugly-side-effects-eating-potato-chips/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">ugly side effects of eating chips</a>. That's why you need to know more about what you're consuming when you opt for this potentially problematic snack.</p><p>\\"If chips are something you want to consume, you should be mindful of portion sizes, how much fat and sodium the serving size contributes, and any other unwanted added ingredients the chips may contain,\\" <strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://kcampbellnutrition.com/\\">Kiran Campbell, RD</a></strong>, tells <em>Eat This, Not That! </em>\\"Most brands of chips on the market do contain fat and a decent amount of sodium and calories, which may make them the unhealthiest component of your meal. For this reason, you should always look at the nutritional content located on the nutrition facts label,\\" advises Campbell.</p><p>When you do, be sure to \\"avoid any brands or flavors that are high in sodium, saturated, or trans fats,\\" adds Campbell. \\"You may also want to avoid chips with added dyes which can be used for coloring.\\"</p><p>With that in mind, you'll want to check out the following options, which are some of the unhealthiest chips you should absolutely steer clear of.</p><p>RELATED: <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/unhealthiest-foods-on-the-planet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">72 Unhealthiest Foods on the Planet</a></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":98,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAUCotS.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"4. Mindless eating","caption":"<p><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/bad-eating-habits-to-stop-immediately/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">Mindless eating</a> habits affect us in sneaky ways. Sometimes, not being fully present at your meals results in not being completely satisfied. You might notice cravings later despite already eating a meal or <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/high-protein-breakfasts/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">feeling full</a> if you weren't mindful while eating.</p><p>To practice mindfulness, remove distractions like TV, your phone, or other disruptions. Fritos Chili Cheese Flavored Corn Chips","body":"<p><div class=\\"nutrinfo-black\\"><span>Per serving of about 31 chips or 28 g</span>: 160 calories, 10 g fat (1.5 g saturated fat, 0 g trans fat), 210 mg sodium, 16 g carbs (1 g fiber, <1 g sugar), 2 g protein</div>  </p><p>If you love chili as much as you love cheese and corn chips, <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.fritos.com/products/fritos-chili-cheese-flavored-corn-chips\\">Fritos Chili Cheese Flavored Corn Chips</a> may seem like a savory taste bud-pleasing dream. Unfortunately, no matter how much you adore this offering from the popular brand, it's not something that you should be eating every day.</p><p>\\"Per serving size of 31 chips, this provides an outrageous 10 milligrams of total fat with 1.5 milligrams of saturated fat,\\" Campbell says to explain why these Fritos are among the unhealthiest chips on store shelves. Although that's enough of a reason to only enjoy these occasionally (if ever) she points out that \\"the sodium amount of 210 milligrams per serving is also something that may lead to water retention for some consumers with certain health issues.\\"</p><p><em>Make better eating choices every day by signing up for our <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/newsletters?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">newsletter</a>!</em></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":85,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1a39sc.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"1. Cheetos Minis Flamin Hot Bites","body":"<p><div class=\\"nutrinfo-black\\"><span>Per serving of 63 pieces or 28 g</span>: 160 calories, 10 g fat (1.5 g saturated fat), 260 mg sodium, 15 g carbs (1 g fiber, 0 g sugar), 1 g protein</div>  </p><p>If you haven't heard of <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.fritolayminis.com/products/cheetosr-minis-flamin-hot\\">Cheetos Minis Flamin Hot Bites</a>, that's because they \\"are newer on the market,\\" according to Campbell, who points out that they are \\"also an unhealthy choice.\\"</p><p>\\"A serving size of 63 tiny Cheeto balls gives 10 grams of total fat, 1.5 grams saturated fat, and 260 milligrams sodium,\\" she explains.</p><p>\\"The ingredients list also states that the Flamin' Hot seasoning contains artificial coloring, including Red 40 Lake and multiple yellow dyes,\\" Campbell says while bringing up another issue with this particular variety of Cheetos. Although that may not seem like much of a problem, Red 40 has been linked to a range of side effects including allergic reactions, asthma, skin irritation, migraines, and hyperactivity, as well as changes in mood such as feeling depressed or irritable, according to the <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://health.clevelandclinic.org/red-dye-40/\\">Cleveland Clinic</a>.</p><p>On top of that, <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/news-surprising-truth-about-msg/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">MSG</a> (or monosodium glutamate) is another ingredient found in Cheetos Minis Flamin Hot Bites, which Campbell says \\"some consumers may be sensitive to.\\"</p><p>RELATED: <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/red-40-food-dye-bowel-disease-study/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">Food Dye in Twizzlers, Doritos, & More Foods May Trigger Bowel Diseases, Study Finds</a></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1a39se.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"2. They are the foods that make you feel warm, full, nostalgic, and happy. But sometimes those often carb-laden comfort dishes don't always align with certain diets. Additionally, finding <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/foods-to-avoid-keto-diet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">keto-friendly</a> comfort food recipes, in particular, can sometimes prove to be especially difficult.</p><p>The keto diet is a very specific diet plan that involves eating foods that have either no or very few carbohydrates, as well as foods that are high in fat. This helps the body to stay in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ketosis-tips-keto-diet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">ketosis</a>, in which your body doesn't consume enough carbohydrates during the day to burn for energy, so it burns fat instead.</p><p>Followers of the keto diet tend to avoid foods with a lot of sugar in them or those made from grains. However, this can limit your ability to enjoy a lot of classic comfort food dishes.</p><p>Thankfully, there are always workarounds to help make a meal keto-friendly. They are the foods that make you feel warm, full, nostalgic, and happy. But sometimes those often carb-laden comfort dishes don't always align with certain diets. Additionally, finding <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/foods-to-avoid-keto-diet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">keto-friendly</a> comfort food recipes, in particular, can sometimes prove to be especially difficult.</p><p>The keto diet is a very specific diet plan that involves eating foods that have either no or very few carbohydrates, as well as foods that are high in fat. This helps the body to stay in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ketosis-tips-keto-diet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">ketosis</a>, in which your body doesn't consume enough carbohydrates during the day to burn for energy, so it burns fat instead.</p><p>Followers of the keto diet tend to avoid foods with a lot of sugar in them or those made from grains. However, this can limit your ability to enjoy a lot of classic comfort food dishes.</p><p>Thankfully, there are always workarounds to help make a meal keto-friendly. This means that the carbohydrates within yams are broken down slowly, which allows for a slow and steady release of sugar into the bloodstream. Dry mouth is a common cause of bad breath because saliva helps wash away bacteria in the mouth,\\" she explains. \\"When you're dehydrated, your mouth produces less saliva, which can lead to bad breath. Eating cucumbers can help hydrate the mouth, increasing saliva production and helping to wash away bacteria.\\"</p><p>\\"[Also], <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23098877/\\">cucumbers contain phytochemicals</a>, such as polyphenols and flavonoids, that have antioxidant properties,\\" adds Burdeos adds. \\"These compounds help reduce the number of bacteria in the mouth that can cause bad breath.\\"</p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":98,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAVwuQP.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"10. Though generally considered a less-than-nutritious treat, <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/healthy-chips/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">some chips are healthier</a> than others, and the unhealthiest chips of all can be especially difficult to resist. If you grab too many bags and nibble on these treats a little too often, you might end up dealing with the <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ugly-side-effects-eating-potato-chips/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">ugly side effects of eating chips</a>. That's why you need to know more about what you're consuming when you opt for this potentially problematic snack.</p><p>\\"If chips are something you want to consume, you should be mindful of portion sizes, how much fat and sodium the serving size contributes, and any other unwanted added ingredients the chips may contain,\\" <strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://kcampbellnutrition.com/\\">Kiran Campbell, RD</a></strong>, tells <em>Eat This, Not That! </em>\\"Most brands of chips on the market do contain fat and a decent amount of sodium and calories, which may make them the unhealthiest component of your meal. For this reason, you should always look at the nutritional content located on the nutrition facts label,\\" advises Campbell.</p><p>When you do, be sure to \\"avoid any brands or flavors that are high in sodium, saturated, or trans fats,\\" adds Campbell. \\"You may also want to avoid chips with added dyes which can be used for coloring.\\"</p><p>With that in mind, you'll want to check out the following options, which are some of the unhealthiest chips you should absolutely steer clear of.</p><p>RELATED: <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/unhealthiest-foods-on-the-planet/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">72 Unhealthiest Foods on the Planet</a></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":98,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAUCotS.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"4. Mindless eating","caption":"<p><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/bad-eating-habits-to-stop-immediately/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">Mindless eating</a> habits affect us in sneaky ways. Sometimes, not being fully present at your meals results in not being completely satisfied. You might notice cravings later despite already eating a meal or <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/high-protein-breakfasts/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">feeling full</a> if you weren't mindful while eating.</p><p>To practice mindfulness, remove distractions like TV, your phone, or other disruptions. Focus on your senses while you eat. Chew slowly and spend time savoring your food.</p><p>Notice whether or not you feel more satisfied by the end of the meal!</p>","source":"msn"}},{"title":"1. Fritos Chili Cheese Flavored Corn Chips","body":"<p><div class=\\"nutrinfo-black\\"><span>Per serving of about 31 chips or 28 g</span>: 160 calories, 10 g fat (1.5 g saturated fat, 0 g trans fat), 210 mg sodium, 16 g carbs (1 g fiber, <1 g sugar), 2 g protein</div>  </p><p>If you love chili as much as you love cheese and corn chips, <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.fritos.com/products/fritos-chili-cheese-flavored-corn-chips\\">Fritos Chili Cheese Flavored Corn Chips</a> may seem like a savory taste bud-pleasing dream. Unfortunately, no matter how much you adore this offering from the popular brand, it's not something that you should be eating every day.</p><p>\\"Per serving size of 31 chips, this provides an outrageous 10 milligrams of total fat with 1.5 milligrams of saturated fat,\\" Campbell says to explain why these Fritos are among the unhealthiest chips on store shelves. Although that's enough of a reason to only enjoy these occasionally (if ever) she points out that \\"the sodium amount of 210 milligrams per serving is also something that may lead to water retention for some consumers with certain health issues.\\"</p><p><em>Make better eating choices every day by signing up for our <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/newsletters?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">newsletter</a>!</em></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":85,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1a39sc.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"1. Candy","body":"<p>Overdoing it on sweet treats isn't a smart move for all sorts of health issues, gut health included. \\"We know that a diet high in sugar has many downstream health effects, but often, folks forget gut health,\\" says <strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"http://carolinethomason.com/\\">Caroline Thomason, RD, CDCES</a></strong>. \\"A <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7284805/\\">high-sugar diet</a> can disrupt the balance of good and bad gut bugs and may contribute to worsening gastrointestinal symptoms like bloating, gas, pain, and loose stools.\\"</p><p>Fortunately, that doesn't mean all desserts are bad news for your belly. Additionally, there's not much nutrition besides simple carbohydrates\xE2\x80\x94which means that you might find yourself with high blood sugar and still hungry, and that never feels very good.</p><p>\\"Watch the candies. Delicious, Healthy Lunch Recipes for Weight Loss","abstract":"These protein and fiber-packed meals will keep you full until dinner.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/35-delicious-healthy-lunch-recipes-for-weight-loss/ss-AA14KJm0","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>When it\xE2\x80\x99s midday and you realize your stomach is already growling, the last thing you want to do is find a place to get a healthful meal. You\xE2\x80\x99re hungry, and it\xE2\x80\x99s just so convenient to head to the office cafeteria for whatever they have to offer. But if your goal is losing weight, planning healthy lunch ideas for <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/weight-loss/diets/g20440614/25-best-weight-loss-tips-ever/\\">weight loss</a> to have at the ready makes the biggest difference in supporting your goals.</p><p>And skipping out on lunch is never an option. \xE2\x80\x9CIt\xE2\x80\x99s unfair to expect our body or brain to perform at their best if we aren\xE2\x80\x99t providing the fuel they need through food,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://streetsmartnutrition.com/about/\\">Cara Harbstreet, M.S., R.D., L.D.</a>, owner of <a href=\\"http://www.streetsmartnutrition.com\\">Street Smart Nutrition</a>. \xE2\x80\x9CSkipping a mid-day meal eliminates a key opportunity to get essential nutrition or food groups that may not show up in other meals or snacks.\xE2\x80\x9D </p><h2>How to build a healthy lunch for weight loss</h2><p>The most important thing to keep in mind when planning your lunches for the week is choosing foods that taste good to you, make you feel good, and keep you satisfied, says <a href=\\"https://beautifuleatsandthings.com/about/\\">Andrea Mathis, M.A., R.D.N., L.D.N.</a>, author of <a href=\\"https://www.amazon.com/Complete-Book-Smoothies-Healthy-Energize-ebook/dp/B091MDL2J5?tag=syndication-20&ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2141.g.42100898%5Bsrc%7Cmsn-us\\"><em>The Complete Book of Smoothies</em></a>. Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. Your plate should include fiber, fat, and protein to promote the feeling of fullness and manage appetite.
